                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.4556/9–3049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Callanan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-30">September 30,
                            1949.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 30—8:39 a. m]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>363. This is last message, transmitter and receiver closing down today. ConGen
                    closing October 1. Department please inform all China posts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Callanan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
